    <forecast>
        <area aac="SA_FA001" description="South Australia" type="region">
            <forecast-period start-time-local="2026-05-15T21:16:41+09:30" end-time-local="2026-05-15T21:16:41+09:30" start-time-utc="2026-05-15T11:46:41Z" end-time-utc="2026-05-15T11:46:41Z">
                <text type="warning_summary_footer">For latest warnings go to www.bom.gov.au, subscribe to RSS feeds, call 1300 659 210* or listen for warnings on relevant TV and radio broadcasts.</text>
                <text type="synoptic_situation">A strong high pressure system in the Tasman Sea continues to move east. A cold front and trough will move over SA on the weekend. Another cold front will move over the south early next week, followed by a high pressure system.</text>
                <text type="product_footer">* Calls to 1300 numbers cost around 27.5c incl. GST, higher from mobiles or public phones.</text>
            </forecast-period>
        </area>
        <area aac="SA_PW015" description="Mount Lofty Ranges" type="public-district" parent-aac="SA_FA001">
            <forecast-period index="0" start-time-local="2026-05-15T21:00:00+09:30" end-time-local="2026-05-16T00:00:00+09:30" start-time-utc="2026-05-15T11:30:00Z" end-time-utc="2026-05-15T14:30:00Z">
                <text type="forecast">Cloudy. High chance of rain. The chance of a thunderstorm about the southern Fleurieu Peninsula. Winds northerly 15 to 25 km/h.</text>
            </forecast-period>
            <forecast-period index="1" start-time-local="2026-05-16T00:00:00+09:30" end-time-local="2026-05-17T00:00:00+09:30" start-time-utc="2026-05-15T14:30:00Z" end-time-utc="2026-05-16T14:30:00Z">
                <text type="forecast">Partly cloudy. Very high chance of showers, most likely in the morning. The chance of a thunderstorm in the afternoon and evening. Winds northerly 15 to 25 km/h tending northwesterly in the morning then becoming light in the early afternoon. Overnight temperatures falling to around 13 with daytime temperatures reaching between 18 and 21.</text>
                <text type="uv_alert">Sun protection 11:10am to 1:00pm, UV Index predicted to reach 3 [Moderate]</text>
            </forecast-period>
            <forecast-period index="2" start-time-local="2026-05-17T00:00:00+09:30" end-time-local="2026-05-18T00:00:00+09:30" start-time-utc="2026-05-16T14:30:00Z" end-time-utc="2026-05-17T14:30:00Z">
                <text type="forecast">Partly cloudy. The chance of morning fog. Medium chance of showers, most likely in the late morning and afternoon. Light winds. Overnight temperatures falling to around 11 with daytime temperatures reaching between 17 and 20.</text>
            </forecast-period>
            <forecast-period index="3" start-time-local="2026-05-18T00:00:00+09:30" end-time-local="2026-05-19T00:00:00+09:30" start-time-utc="2026-05-17T14:30:00Z" end-time-utc="2026-05-18T14:30:00Z">
                <text type="forecast">Partly cloudy. The chance of morning fog. Medium chance of showers, most likely in the evening. Light winds becoming westerly 15 to 20 km/h during the afternoon then tending northwesterly during the evening. Overnight temperatures falling to around 10 with daytime temperatures reaching between 16 and 19.</text>
            </forecast-period>
            <forecast-period index="4" start-time-local="2026-05-19T00:00:00+09:30" end-time-local="2026-05-20T00:00:00+09:30" start-time-utc="2026-05-18T14:30:00Z" end-time-utc="2026-05-19T14:30:00Z">
                <text type="forecast">Partly cloudy. High chance of showers, most likely in the morning and afternoon. Winds west to northwesterly 15 to 20 km/h turning southwesterly 15 to 25 km/h during the morning. Overnight temperatures falling to between 9 and 12 with daytime temperatures reaching between 15 and 19.</text>
            </forecast-period>
        </area>
